           img(src="images/create/create9.png")
      
      section
         h1 Save your Presentation
      
      section
         h2 Save File
         ul
           li PowerPoint offers two ways to save a file: Save and Save As. 
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
           li Save: When you create or edit a presentation, you'll use the Save command to save your changes. You'll use this command most of the time.
           li Save As: You'll use this command to create a copy of a presentation while keeping the original.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 To save a presentation:
         ul
           li You'll also need to pay close attention to where you save the presentation so it will be easy to find later.
         p
           li Locate and select the Save command on the Quick Access Toolbar.
            img(src="images/save/save1.png")
           li If you're saving the file for the first time, the Save As pane will appear in Backstage view.
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
           li To save the presentation to your computer, select Computer, then click Browse. Alternatively, you can click OneDrive to save the file to your OneDrive.
             img(src="images/save/save2.png")
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
           li The Save As dialog box will appear. Select the location where you wish to save the presentation.
           li Enter a file name for the presentation, then click Save.
             img(src="images/save/save3.png")

      section
          li The presentation will be saved. You can click the Save command again to save your changes as you modify the presentation.
          li You can also access the Save command by pressing CTRL+S on your keyboard

